===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|ic}}. Two forms can be found in oracle bone script:
# {{Han compound|爪|t1=hand|果|t2=fruit}} – a hand ({{l|zh|爪}}) picking fruits from a tree ({{l|zh|果}}).
# {{Han compound|爪|t1=hand|木|t2=tree}} – a hand ({{l|zh|爪}}) picking from a tree ({{l|zh|木}}).
The current glyph is of composition 2.

===Etymology 1===
{{unc|zh}}. Several etymologies have been proposed:
* From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tsa-n||child; grandchild; nephew; niece}}, whence {{cog|bo|བཙའ|t=to fruit, bear, bring forth}}, {{m|bo|བཙས|t=to harvest, to reap}}, possibly as well as {{och-l|才}}, {{och-l|子}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
* Related to {{cog|bo|ཚོད་མ||vegetables}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
* Related to {{och-l|穡|tr=*s.rək|to reap; harvest}} ({{zh-ref|Baxter, 1992}}; {{zh-ref|Sagart, 1999}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}).

